From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 07:53:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Docs/admin-guide/mm/damon/usage: update for counters of
 interests ABI

Allow users to set multiple interests, or sample types per context.
Each interest has multiple filters to distinguish what page they have
interest.  The filter supports multiple sampling primitives including
page table a-bit check, page faults check, perf events, and the DAMOS
filter-supporting types.  One of the filters can have 'primary' field.

Each region has a counter per the user-added interest.  For each
sampling interval, the counter for interests are incremented if they
pass the filters of the interest.  Regions are adapted for 'primary'
interest.

The counters are exposed via after_aggregation tracepoint and DAMOS
tried regions.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
